.TH dialogfetchmailmon 1 "@PACKAGE@ @VERSION@"
.SH NAME
dialogfetchmailmon \- 'dialog' interface to txtfetchmailmon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.BI "dialogfetchmailmon [-size|-number] [file]"
.sp
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B dialogfetchmailmon
is a simple interface to
.B "txtfetchmailmon"\c.
It uses the
.B dialog
program to display a progression bar.

.B dialogfetchmailmon
uses
.B txtfetchmailmon
to process mail.log file and extract data.
If
.B txtfetchmailmon
is not on you path (testing?) you can set the
.I TXTFETCHMAILMON
environment variable.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-size
The progression bar represents a percentage based on the email sizes.
This is most representative of the time to go.
.TP
\-number
The progression bar represents a percentage based on the number of emails.
(DEFAULT)
.TP
file
Monitor this file instead of default one (@DEFAULT_MAILLOG_FILENAME@).

.SH FILES
.TP
@DEFAULT_MAILLOG_FILENAME@
The default system messages file read.

.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR fetchmail (1),
.BR dialog (1),
.BR txtfetchmailmon (1)

